                                  uip or jobs                                   
Manage UiPath Orchestrator jobs (process executions). Start jobs from processes, monitor execution, check logs and traces.
                Use --help with nested commands for more detail.                

┌─ Usage ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ uip or jobs [options] [command]                                              │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

┌─ Commands ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ get            Get a job by its key (GUID). Returns state, input/output      │
│                arguments, timing, machine info, and error details if         │
│                faulted. If the job is in Pending state, also includes        │
│                diagnostic reasons (robot availability, capacity, etc.). No   │
│                folder context needed — the key is globally unique. Use 'jobs │
│                list' to find job keys.                                       │
│ healing-data   Download healing agent (Autopilot for Robots) recovery data   │
│                as a ZIP file. Contains screenshots, UI element data, and     │
│                recovery logs. Only available for jobs where the healing      │
│                agent was active. Triggers an async export, polls until       │
│                complete, then downloads the ZIP.                             │
│ help           display help for command                                      │
│ history        Get state transition history for a job. Shows timestamps for  │
│                each state change (Pending → Running → Successful/Faulted).   │
│                Useful for understanding job lifecycle and identifying        │
│                delays. Folder context is resolved automatically from the job │
│                key.                                                          │
│ list           List jobs. Returns job key, state, process name, timing, and  │
│                machine info. Use --state to filter by job state (Pending,    │
│                Running, Successful, Faulted, Stopped, Stopping, Suspended,   │
│                Resumed, Terminating). Provide --folder-path or --folder-key  │
│                to scope to a folder, or omit for cross-folder listing.       │
│ logs           Get robot execution logs for a job. Filter by --level to      │
│                quickly find errors. Folder context is inferred from the job  │
│                key. Logs are returned newest-first.                          │
│ restart        Restart a faulted or stopped job. Creates a new job from the  │
│                same process. No folder context needed — resolved from job    │
│                key.                                                          │
│ resume         Resume a suspended job. Jobs become suspended when they use   │
│                the 'Suspend' activity (long-running workflows that wait for  │
│                external input). Optionally pass new --input-arguments to     │